      <h1 class='title'>Circumstances in which orders made under this Part may be made</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c296GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_296gc' title='Col. 296GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c296GC' name='column_296gc' href='#column_296gc' rel='bookmark'>296GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03844'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_455' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        1 (1) On an application to it by one of the civil partners, the court may make any one or more of the orders set out in paragraph 2 if it is satisfied that the other civil partner&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) has failed to provide reasonable maintenance for the applicant,</li>
        <li>(b) has failed to provide, or to make a proper contribution towards, reasonable maintenance for any child of the family,</li>
        <li>(c) has behaved in such a way that the applicant cannot reasonably be expected to live with the respondent, or</li>
        <li>(d) has deserted the applicant.</li></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03845'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_456' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) The power of the court under sub-paragraph (1) is subject to the following provisions of this Schedule.
      </p>
      <ol class='xoxo'>
        
      </ol>
      
